### BFF Mobile Login API - Ejemplos de uso

### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@cuit = 20123456789
@email = comercio@example.com
@password = MiPassword123!

### 1. Crear Suscripción
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/private/subscriptions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "cuit": "{{cuit}}"
}

### 2. Validar Suscripción (con OTP recibido por email)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/v1/private/subscriptions/{{cuit}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "otp": "123456"
}

### 3. Reenviar Challenge OTP
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/v1/private/subscriptions/{{cuit}}

### 4. Crear Cuenta (usando la key de la suscripción validada)
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/private/accounts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "cuit": "{{cuit}}",
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}",
  "firstName": "Juan",
  "lastName": "Pérez",
  "key": "123e4567-e89b-12d3-a456-426614174000"
}

### 5. Login
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/private/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### 6. Login con Refresh Token
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/private/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}",
  "refreshToken": "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9..."
}

### 7. Ver documentación Swagger
GET {{baseUrl}}/api

